1\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Kaduy, Vologda Oblast|Kaduy]] is 30&nbsp;km, to Nikolskoye is 6&nbsp;km. Budimorovo is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Kaduysky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Kaduysky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Ivanovo\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Kaduysky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|23|N|37|10|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/kaduyskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u041a\u0430\u0434\u0443\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Ivanovo''' ({{lang-ru|\u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Nikolskoye Rural Settlement, [[Kaduysky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 7 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Kaduy, Vologda Oblast|Kaduy]] is 30&nbsp;km, to Nikolskoye is 6&nbsp;km. Budimorovo is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Kaduysky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Kaduysky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivanovo,_Kaduysky_District,_Vologda_Oblast"}
{"title_page": "Vugar Bayramov", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{More footnotes|BLP=yes|date=January 2018}}\n{{External links|date=January 2018}}}}\n{{Infobox economist\n | image         = Deputy Bayramov.jpg\n | caption       = \n | name          = Vugar Bayramov\n | birth_date    = June 13, 1975\n | birth_place   = [[Fuzuli District, Azerbaijan]]\n | death_date    = \n | death_place   = \n | field         = Macroeconomics, energy economics\n | institution   = Azerbaijan State Economic University\n | alma_mater    = Washington University in St. Louis\n | influences    = \n | influenced    = \n | contributions = \n}}\n\n'''Vugar Bayramov'' ('''V\u00fcqar Bayramov'' in Azerbaijani) (born June 13, 1975 in [[Ashagi Guzlek]] village of [[Fuzuli District]]) is an economist in [[Azerbaijan]]. He has a Ph.D. in economics. He was the visiting faculty member at [[Washington University]], U.S. in 2003 and 2004. Vugar Bayramov is also alumnus of [[Austrian Leadership Programs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bmeia.gv.at/en/european-foreign-policy/foreign-trade-promotion/alps/|title=ALPs \u2013 BMEIA, Au\u00dfenministerium \u00d6sterreich|first=Au\u00dfenministerium der Republik|last=\u00d6sterreich|website=Bmeia.gv.at|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAs the chairman of [[The Center for Economic and Social Development]], a leading economic think tank in [[Azerbaijan]], Dr. Bayramov has conducted various research projects on both macro and micro economics in the areas of local government, municipality development, state budget transparency, etc.\n\nVugar Bayramov is the founder of the first [[think tank]] in [[Azerbaijan]]. [[The Center for Economic and Social Development]], the first think tank in Azerbaijan, is the top think tank in [[South Caucasus]] and [[Central Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thinktankwatch.com/2016/01/2016-think-tank-rankings-cheat-sheet.html|title=2016 Think Tank Rankings - Cheat Sheet|website=Thinktankwatch.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}</ref> His center has been ranked as the top think tank not only in Azerbaijan but also in the region by the University of Pennsylvania, USA.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McGann |first1=James G. |title=2015 Global Go To Think Tank Index Report |year=2016 |work=TTCSP Global Go To Think Tank Index Reports |url=http://repository.upenn.edu/think_tanks/10 }}</ref>\n\nHis most recent papers were published by [[Communist and Post-Communist Studies]] in [[United States]], [[Resources Policy]] in [[UK]], and [[Bilig]] in [[Turkey]],<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Vugar |last1=Bayramov |first2=Laman |last2=Orujova |year=2017 |title=Volatility, Diversification and Oil Shock in Resource-Rich Turkic Countries: Avenues for Recovery |journal=Bilig |volume=83 |pages=303\u201329 |url=http://bilig.yesevi.edu.tr/yonetim/icerik/makaleler/2080-published.pdf }}</ref> in 2017. All indicated journals are indexed by [[Thomson Reuters]]. He is the author of \u201cOil Revenues Usage Strategy in Azerbaijan\u201d Project. Bayramov is also a lecturer at [[Azerbaijan State Economic University]], where he teaches economics and finance courses.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nBayramov was the first Azerbaijani co-chair of  [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership [[Civil Society Forum]].<ref name=\"epd.eu\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.epd.eu/eastern-partnership-civil-society-forum |title=Archived copy |access-date=January 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720161210/http://www.epd.eu/eastern-partnership-civil-society-forum |archive-date=July 20, 2011 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He has been also National Coordinator of the [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership Civil Society Forum in [[Azerbaijan]].<ref name=\"epd.eu\"/> He is a member of the [[Steering Committee]] of [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership Program which includes 6 partner countries: [[Azerbaijan]], [[Armenia]], [[Belarus]], [[Georgia (country)|Republic of Georgia]], [[Moldova]] and [[Ukraine]].\n\nBayramov is one of the most 500 influential Muslims in the world reported by The Royal Islamic Strategic Studies Centre  (RISSC) in [[Jordan]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rissc.jo/docs/0A-FullVersion-LowRes.pdf|format=PDF|title=THE 500 MOST INFLUENTIAL MUSLIMS : 2010|website=Rissc.jo|accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBayramov was born on in Azerbaijan on June 13, 1975. He received his first university degree in [[Baku]] in [[Azerbaijan]] in 1997. His parents were educators at a secondary school. Vugar Bayramov obtained his master's degree from [[Azerbaijan State Economic University]] in 1999 and then [[Washington University]] in 2004. Dr. Bayramov is fluent in English, Russian, [[Turkish language|Turkish]] and [[Azeri]]; he can also speak French and Spanish. Vugar Bayramov is the chairman of [[the Center for Economic and Social Development]], a leading economic [[think tank]] in Azerbaijan.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n===Regional activities===\nBayramov is the author of Anti-Crisis Concept Project of Azerbaijan Republic<ref>[http://www.cesd.az/crisis.pdf] {{dead link|date=January 2018}}</ref> where stated policy recommendations were adopted by the government. As one of leading economic experts in the region, Vugar Bayramov has been several times involved in developing state programs including anti-crisis programs by [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] Countries Governments.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n==Writings==\n===Papers===\nBayramov's papers have been published in several leading journals and newspapers in the world. He is very often invited to serve as a speaker in very prestigious global conferences. Many leading mass-media institutes including [[BBC]], Izvestiya, Times, [[Voice of America]] and others have referenced Dr. Bayramov's comments and feedbacks on regional economic issues. Vugar Bayramov has been awarded with several medals by different countries governments. He was the first from Azerbaijan invited to attend the [[WTO]] 6th Ministerial Conference in [[Hong-Kong]] in 2005.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n===Articles===\nHis articles have been published in 19 different languages. He is the author of more than eight books published in English, Russian and other languages.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Vugar Bayramov, ed. ''[http://www.cesd.az/documents/book.pdf Ending Dependency: How Is Oil Revenues Effectively Used in Azerbaijan?]'' ({{ISBN|978-9952-8131-0-4}})\n* Vugar Bayramov, ''Health Economics''\n* Vugar Bayramov, ''Social Insurance in Azerbaijan: Diagnostics and Recommendations on Policy and Implementation'' ({{ISBN|978-9952-8131-3-5}})\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=http://ictsd.net/i/news/bridgesrussian/55823/|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c\u044b, \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u0410\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043a \u0412\u0422\u041e - International Centre for Trade and Sustainable Development|website=Ictsd.net|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/160173/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u0410\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u044e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0432 \u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e|first=\u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|last=\u0423\u0437\u0435\u043b|website=Kavkaz-uzel.ru|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.centrasia.ru/newsA.php?st=1253334000|title=\u0412.\u0411\u0430\u0439\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432: \u0421\u041d\u0413 \u043e\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043b \u0441 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0435\u0440|website=Centrasia.ru|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.respublika-kaz.info/news/finance/5404/|title=NamesPro.ca - Register with Confidenc|website=Respublika-kaz.info|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.silverbearcafe.com/private/caspian.html|title=The Silver Bear Cafe|website=Silverbearcafe.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.slideworld.com/slideshows.aspx/Globalization-and-Inequality-in-CIS-Countries-ppt-299308|title=Globalization and Inequality in CIS Countries  Powerpoint Presentation|website=Slideworld.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.cesd.az|title=Center for Economic and Social Development (CESD)|website=Cesd.az|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.13iacc.org/files/6_4_citizens_against_corruption_final_report.doc|title=13TH INTERNATIONAL ANTI-CORRUPTION CONFERENCE|website=13iacc.org|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://ada.edu.az/biweekly/issues/150/20090327031648590.html|title=Biweekly|website=Ada.edu.az|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.theoildrum.com/node/3431|title=The Oil Drum - DrumBeat: December 25, 2007|website=Theoildrum.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://bilig.yesevi.edu.tr/yonetim/icerik/makaleler/2080-published.pdf|format=PDF|title=Volatility, Diversification and Oil Shock in Resource-Rich Turkic Countries : Avenues for Recovery|author1=Vugar Bayramov|author2=Laman Orujova|website=Bilig.yesevi.edu.tr|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTRAD/Resources/Bayramov.pdf|format=PDF|title=A COMPARATIVE ANALYSIS OF CIS COUNTRIES\u2019 WTO ACCESSION; WAYS TO EUROPEAN INTEGRATION|author=Vugar Bayramov|website=Siteresources.worldbank.org|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.changing-europe.org/download/Summer_School_2008/Bayramov.pdf|format=PDF|author=Vugar Bayramov|title=How To Use Oil Revenues Effectively in Azerbaijan|website=Changing-europe.org|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTSOCACCDEMSIDEGOV/Resources/CESDPresentation_VugarBayramov.pdf|format=PDF|title=Public Expenditure Tracking; Increasing of Role of Communities and Municipalities|website=Siteresources.worldbank.org|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.thewif.org.uk/wif/Kazakhstan/2.pdf|format=PDF|title=List of Kazakh Participants|website=Thewif.org.uk|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.changing-Europe.org/download/Bremen2008-programme.pdf|format=PDF|title=3rd Changing Europe Summer School : Central and Eastern Europe in a globalised world|website=Changing-europe.org|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bayramov, Vugar}}\n[[Category:Azerbaijani economists]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Washington University in St. Louis alumni]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan State University of Economics faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{More footnotes|BLP=yes|date=January 2018}}\n{{External links|date=January 2018}}}}\n{{Infobox economist\n | image = \n[[File:Deputy Bayramov.jpg|thumb]]\n | caption =\n | name = Vugar Bayramov\n | birth_date = June 13, 1975\n | birth_place =\n | death_date =\n | death_place =\n | nationality = [[Azerbaijan]]\n | field = Macroeconomics, Energy Economics\n | institution = Azerbaijan State Economic University\n | alma_mater = Washington University in St. Louis\n | influences =\n | influenced =\n | contributions =\n}}\n\n'''Vugar Bayramov'' ('''V\u00fcqar Bayramov'' in Azerbaijani) (born June 13, 1975 in Ashagi Guzlek village of Fuzuli District ) is an economist in [[Azerbaijan]]. He has a Ph.D. in economics. He was the visiting faculty member at [[Washington University]], USA in 2003 and 2004. Vugar Bayramov is also alumnus of [[Austrian Leadership Programs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bmeia.gv.at/en/european-foreign-policy/foreign-trade-promotion/alps/|title=ALPs \u2013 BMEIA, Au\u00dfenministerium \u00d6sterreich|first=Au\u00dfenministerium der Republik|last=\u00d6sterreich|website=Bmeia.gv.at|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAs the chairman of [[The Center for Economic and Social Development]], a leading economic think tank in [[Azerbaijan]], Dr. Bayramov has conducted various research projects on both macro and micro economics in the areas of local government, municipality development, state budget transparency, etc.\n\nVugar Bayramov is the founder of the first [[think tank]] in [[Azerbaijan]]. [[The Center for Economic and Social Development]], the first think tank in Azerbaijan, is the top think tank in [[South Caucasus]] and [[Central Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thinktankwatch.com/2016/01/2016-think-tank-rankings-cheat-sheet.html|title=2016 Think Tank Rankings - Cheat Sheet|website=Thinktankwatch.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}</ref> His center has been ranked as the top think tank not only in Azerbaijan but also in the region by the University of Pennsylvania, USA.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McGann |first1=James G. |title=2015 Global Go To Think Tank Index Report |year=2016 |work=TTCSP Global Go To Think Tank Index Reports |url=http://repository.upenn.edu/think_tanks/10 }}</ref>\n\nHis most recent papers were published by [[Communist and Post-Communist Studies]] in [[United States]], [[Resources Policy]] in [[UK]], and [[Bilig]] in [[Turkey]],<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Vugar |last1=Bayramov |first2=Laman |last2=Orujova |year=2017 |title=Volatility, Diversification and Oil Shock in Resource-Rich Turkic Countries: Avenues for Recovery |journal=Bilig |volume=83 |pages=303\u201329 |url=http://bilig.yesevi.edu.tr/yonetim/icerik/makaleler/2080-published.pdf }}</ref> in 2017. All indicated journals are indexed by [[Thomson Reuters]]. He is the author of \u201cOil Revenues Usage Strategy in Azerbaijan\u201d Project. Bayramov is also a lecturer at [[Azerbaijan State Economic University]], where he teaches economics and finance courses.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nBayramov was the first Azerbaijani co-chair of  [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership [[Civil Society Forum]].<ref name=\"epd.eu\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.epd.eu/eastern-partnership-civil-society-forum |title=Archived copy |access-date=January 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720161210/http://www.epd.eu/eastern-partnership-civil-society-forum |archive-date=July 20, 2011 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He has been also National Coordinator of the [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership Civil Society Forum in [[Azerbaijan]].<ref name=\"epd.eu\"/> He is a member of the [[Steering Committee]] of [[European Union|EU]] Eastern Partnership Program which includes 6 partner countries: [[Azerbaijan]], [[Armenia]], [[Belarus]], [[Georgia (country)|Republic of Georgia]], [[Moldova]] and [[Ukraine]].\n\nBayramov is one of the most 500 influential Muslims in the world reported by The Royal Islamic Strategic Studies Centre  (RISSC) in [[Jordan]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rissc.jo/docs/0A-FullVersion-LowRes.pdf|format=PDF|title=THE 500 MOST INFLUENTIAL MUSLIMS : 2010|website=Rissc.jo|accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBayramov was born on in Azerbaijan on June 13, 1975. He received his first university degree in [[Baku]] in [[Azerbaijan]] in 1997. His parents were educators at a secondary school. Vugar Bayramov obtained his master's degree from [[Azerbaijan State Economic University]] in 1999 and then [[Washington University]] in 2004. Dr. Bayramov is fluent in English, Russian, [[Turkish language|Turkish]] and [[Azeri]]; he can also speak French and Spanish. Vugar Bayramov is the chairman of [[the Center for Economic and Social Development]], a leading economic [[think tank]] in Azerbaijan.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n===Regional activities===\nBayramov is the author of Anti-Crisis Concept Project of Azerbaijan Republic<ref>[http://www.cesd.az/crisis.pdf] {{dead link|date=January 2018}}</ref> where stated policy recommendations were adopted by the government. As one of leading economic experts in the region, Vugar Bayramov has been several times involved in developing state programs including anti-crisis programs by [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] Countries Governments.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n==Writings==\n===Papers===\nBayramov's papers have been published in several leading journals and newspapers in the world. He is very often invited to serve as a speaker in very prestigious global conferences. Many leading mass-media institutes including [[BBC]], Izvestiya, Times, [[Voice of America]] and others have referenced Dr. Bayramov's comments and feedbacks on regional economic issues. Vugar Bayramov has been awarded with several medals by different countries governments. He was the first from Azerbaijan invited to attend the [[WTO]] 6th Ministerial Conference in [[Hong-Kong]] in 2005.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n===Articles===\nHis articles have been published in 19 different languages. He is the author of more than eight books published in English, Russian and other languages.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Vugar Bayramov, ed. ''[http://www.cesd.az/documents/book.pdf Ending Dependency: How Is Oil Revenues Effectively Used in Azerbaijan?]'' ({{ISBN|978-9952-8131-0-4}})\n* Vugar Bayramov, ''Health Economics''\n* Vugar Bayramov, ''Social Insurance in Azerbaijan: Diagnostics and Recommendations on Policy and Implementation'' ({{ISBN|978-9952-8131-3-5}})\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=http://ictsd.net/i/news/bridgesrussian/55823/|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c\u044b, \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u0410\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043a \u0412\u0422\u041e - International Centre for Trade and Sustainable Development|website=Ictsd.net|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/160173/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u0410\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0430\u0439\u0434\u0436\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u044e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0432 \u043c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e|first=\u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|last=\u0423\u0437\u0435\u043b|website=Kavkaz-uzel.ru|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.centrasia.ru/newsA.php?st=1253334000|title=\u0412.\u0411\u0430\u0439\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432: \u0421\u041d\u0413 \u043e\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043b \u0441 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0435\u0440|website=Centrasia.ru|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.respublika-kaz.info/news/finance/5404/|title=NamesPro.ca - Register with Confidenc|website=Respublika-kaz.info|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.silverbearcafe.com/private/caspian.html|title=The Silver Bear Cafe|website=Silverbearcafe.com|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.slideworld.com/slideshows.aspx/Globalization-and-Inequality-in-CIS-Countries-ppt-299308|title=Globalization and Inequality in CIS Countries  Powerpoint Presentation|website=Slideworld.co